Welcome  

This is an experiment in the economics of decision-making. The instructions are simple; if you follow them carefully and make good decisions, you can earn a considerable amount of money that will be paid to you privately at the end of the experiment.

In this experiment, your color is #id_label#.

You and the other #player_count-1# people in your group each set a consumption range. The ranges you and your group members select determine your earnings each period.

Continue to the next page of the instructions by pressing the Next   button.

Revenue Boxes

Along the horizontal axis there is a set of revenue boxes rising up. The higher the box rises, the more valuable the box is. You and the other members in your group will each submit a contiguous consumption range using the "Start" and "End" handles at the bottom of your screens. You can select any contiguous range, from size one up to the entire range of boxes. However, anywhere your range overlaps with another player in your group, you must split the revenue of that box equally. You must also pay a cost for each box in your range, which we represent on the graph with a light #color_name# color. You will lose money if the cost you pay exceeds the revenue you earn for any given box. Any box you lose money on will display a "!". Boxes outside of all consumption ranges are displayed in white. Boxes within one or more consumption ranges display a stacked graph of the current occupants.

Try moving the range handles. Do this now.

On the next page, we will display the results.

Continue to the next page of the instructions by pressing the Next   button.

Practice

Move the range handles and press the Send Range button at the bottom of your screen. Do this now. Notice how your Cost and Profit changes in the "Group Summary" box at the top of your screen. Try moving your range around and observing how things change. Remember that you will lose money if your cost exceeds your revenue on a box. That is denoted with a "!" on that box.

You and your group members can update your range anytime during the experiment.

Continue to the next page of the instructions by pressing the Next   button.

Conclusion

You can use help buttons to reference the instructions during the experiment.

Once everyone completes the instructions, the ranges will reset. Everyone must press the Ready to Start button at the bottom of the screen before anyone can submit a range.

This is the end of the instructions. If you have any questions, please raise your hand, and a monitor will come by to answer them. If you are finished with the instructions, please click the Start   button located in the bottom right of this frame. The instructions will remain on your screen until the experiment begins. We need everyone to click the Start   button before we can begin the experiment.
